For some of out automates tests (inspired in part by Guavas NullTester) we use a computing map for creating mock objects like so:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Map&lt;Class< ?>, Object> map = new MapMaker().makeComputingMap(new Function&lt;Class< ?>, Object>() {

```
        public Object apply(Class< ?> input) {
            return Mockito.mock(input);
        }

    });
```

I think Guava would be worse off without computing maps personally. This isn't the only use of this, and I understand that its possible to do something similar with the Cache API by turning the cache into a ma but it doesn't seem to be a equally clean solution for certain problems.
